data.content:
Since you need **three** themes, use the **ResourceDictionary swap** approach (`AppThemeBinding` only supports two).

## Setup

### 1. Define three theme dictionaries with matching keys

**Themes/LightTheme.xaml**
```xml
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
                    x:Class="MyApp.Themes.LightTheme">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackgroundColor">White</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryTextColor">#333333</Color>
    <Color x:Key="AccentColor">#2196F3</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

**Themes/DarkTheme.xaml** ã same keys, dark values:
```xml
<Color x:Key="PageBackgroundColor">#1E1E1E</Color>
<Color x:Key="PrimaryTextColor">#F0F0F0</Color>
<Color x:Key="AccentColor">#BB86FC</Color>
```

**Themes/HighContrastTheme.xaml** ã same keys, high-contrast values:
```xml
<Color x:Key="PageBackgroundColor">Black</Color>
<Color x:Key="PrimaryTextColor">Yellow</Color>
<Color x:Key="AccentColor">Cyan</Color>
```

Each needs a code-behind calling `InitializeComponent()`.

### 2. Use `DynamicResource` everywhere (not `StaticResource`)

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackgroundColor}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
    <Button BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource AccentColor}" />
</ContentPage>
```

### 3. Theme switching service

```csharp
public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(string themeName)
    {
        var mergedDictionaries = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDictionaries.Clear();
        mergedDictionaries.Add(themeName switch
        {
            "Dark"         => new DarkTheme(),
            "HighContrast" => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _              => new LightTheme()
        });

        Preferences.Set("AppTheme", themeName);
    }

    public static void RestoreSavedTheme()
    {
        var saved = Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "Light");
        ApplyTheme(saved);
    }
}
```

### 4. Call on startup (App constructor)

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.RestoreSavedTheme();
}
```

### 5. Settings page picker

```csharp
void OnThemeSelected(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    string choice = themePicker.SelectedItem as string; // "Light", "Dark", "HighContrast"
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(choice);
}
```

Changes apply immediately because `DynamicResource` bindings re-evaluate when the merged dictionary changes.

### Key pitfalls to avoid

- **All three dictionaries must define the same `x:Key` set** ã missing keys silently fall back to defaults.
- **Android**: ensure `ConfigChanges.UiMode` is on `MainActivity` to prevent activity restarts.
- **Never use `StaticResource`** for themed values ã they won't update at runtime.
